# Creating Visuals 

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure()
plt.plot(result["days_before_game"], result["avg_clicks"])
plt.xlabel("Days Before Game")
plt.ylabel("Average Page Clicks")
plt.title("Ticket Page Clicks Leading Up to Game Day")
plt.gca().invert_xaxis()
plt.show()

# Explanation: 
- This code creates a line chart that demonstrates the relationship between time before the game and fan engagement.
By showing the average number of ticket page clicks as the game approaches.
The engagement increased in the final days before a game suggesting fans become more active as the event approaches.

